  diff in prokaryotic and eukaryotic cell:

| Prokaryotic Cell                                             | Eukaryotic Cell                                          |
| ------------------------------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1. No true nucleus (nuclear membrane absent)                 | 1. True nucleus present with nuclear membrane            |
| 2. DNA is circular and not associated with histones          | 2. DNA is linear and associated with histone proteins    |
| 3. Membrane-bound organelles absent (e.g., mitochondria, ER) | 3. Membrane-bound organelles present                     |
| 4. Cell size smaller (1–10 µm)                               | 4. Cell size larger (10–100 µm)                          |
| 5. Cell division by binary fission                           | 5. Cell division by mitosis/meiosis                      |
| 6. Ribosomes are 70S                                         | 6. Ribosomes are 80S                                     |
| 7. Mostly unicellular (e.g., bacteria)                       | 7. Mostly multicellular, some unicellular (e.g., amoeba) |

